That brings an end to the innings! India has scored a competitive 265 on this Ahmedabad surface! West Indies started off very well, picking up 3 wickets in the first 10 overs. A century partnership between Pant and Iyer then brought India back into the game. Sundar and Chahar also contributed with fine cameos at the end of the innings to propel India to 265. Jason Holder was the pick of the bowlers with 4-34 from 8 overs. Catch us after the break to see if India can make it 3-0.
